Video_Title: RAW VIDEO: Police chase across Houston in morning rush hour ends in SWAT take down of suspect
Description:
police chase across houston during morning rush hour traffic: http://abc13.com/3245987/

a bizarre, sometimes very slow-speed chase, all began when police say a baytown newlywed threatened his wife of just two weeks.

subscribe to our channel for more news videos.
like us on fb: https://www.facebook.com/abc13houston/
check us out on twitter: http://twitter.com/abc13houston

it all started in baytown as a 911 call for a disturbance at about 7:45 a.m. baytown police say 42-year-old eric brown reportedly threatened his wife with a gun and fired a shot. when officers arrived, the man got into the vehicle and took off, with police in pursuit.
law enforcement agencies pursued brown across the east and south sides of houston, into the galleria area at one point.

police say there were reports that he had a weapon and a self-inflicted gunshot wound.

how to fix the quiet mic problem:

instructions are from here on reddit: https://www.reddit.com/r/corsair/comments/45hh44/corsair_void_rgb_usb_quiet_mic/d00s2wa

1. dowload equalizer apo here: https://sourceforge.net/projects/equalizerapo/files/0.9.2/equalizerapo64-0.9.2.exe/download?use_mirror=netix&download=&failedmirror=kent.dl.sourceforge.net

2. install

3. in the installation folder you will find a program called "configurator". open it

4. you will see two tabs. playback devices and capture devices. find your headset in the capture tab and check the little box then press ok. it will ask you to restart and do it.

5. after restarting go to the equalizer directory again and in the file "config" you will find a text file called "config". open it and in this file you can change the level of the devices you ticked in the configurator program.

zy: so that's what i did, and my config.txt now has this in it:

device: sennheiser communication audio headset earphone {087036d0-ea10-4038-a06b-da7e64abdbb4}
preamp: 0 db
;
device: sennheiser communication audio headset microphone {fc28406d-0e85-4e0c-8140-9c83ae7a440f}
preamp: 14 db 

you can raise that last 14 if it's still too quiet.

david's latest book “drink?” explores the science of alcohol, its detrimental effects on one’s health, and the damage it causes humankind.
